      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHINA TEA EXPORTS THREATENED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stricter environmental standards from European Union threaten $100 million in tea exports from China; new European regulations on pesticides in tea mean Chinese farmers have to stop using bug spray or lose European market (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Stricter environmental standards from the European Union threaten $100 million in tea exports from China, the world's second-largest tea exporter after India. New European regulations on pesticides in tea mean Chinese farmers have to stop using bug spray or lose the European market. A Chinese delegation will visit Brussels to discuss the new regulations.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
